name: Traditional Cappuccino
about: Traditional Cappuccino is made from espresso, hot milk, and steamed milk. It has a thick layer of foam on top and is usually garnished with cocoa powder or pumpkin spice

name: Cappuccino Mocha
about: Cappuccino Mocha is made from espresso, hot milk, steamed milk, and chocolate. It has a thick layer of foam on top and is usually garnished with cocoa powder

name: Black Cold Brew
about: Black Cold Brew is made by steeping coffee grounds in cold water for an extended period. It has a bold, strong flavor and is less acidic than hot-brewed coffee. Black Cold Brew is usually served with ice or milk

name: Cold Brew Latte
about: Cold Brew Latte is made from Cold Brew coffee, milk, and sugar. It has a bold, strong flavor and is less acidic than hot-brewed coffee. Cold Brew Latte is usually served with ice or milk

name: Traditional Espresso
about: Traditional Espresso is made by forcing hot water under high pressure through finely ground coffee beans. It has a layer of reddish-brown crema on top and is usually served in a small cup

name: Espresso Macchiato
about: Espresso Macchiato is made from espresso and a small amount of steamed milk. It has a layer of reddish-brown crema on top and is usually served in a small cup
